sql:
SELECT * 
FROM wafers 
WHERE fabrication_machine = 'MachineB';

SELECT wafer_id, scribe_id, lot_id, inspection_date, wafer_thickness, wafer_diameter, fabrication_date, fabrication_line, fabrication_machine, fabrication_operator
FROM wafers
ORDER BY inspection_date DESC;

SELECT wafer_id
FROM wafers
WHERE lot_id IN (
  SELECT lot_id
  FROM lots
  WHERE total_wafers > (
    SELECT AVG(total_wafers)
    FROM lots
  )
);

external_knowledge:
- 'Typical severity' is understood as the average severity level of defects;
- 'Flaws' refers to 'defects';
- 'Each type of product' corresponds to each unique product name in the database.

- 'Product A' is metaphorically referred to as a banner, symbolizing the identification of a product's identity among many. ;
- The term 'trails of entry' metaphorically refers to the access logs. ;
- 'Historical meetings' metaphorically represents the chronological order of access dates.

sql:
SELECT wafer_id
FROM defects
WHERE severity > 5;

external_knowledge:
- Summer typically ends towards the end of September in many parts of the world;
- "Last year" in this context refers to the year 2019;
- "Created in the later part of the summer" refers to wafers with a fabrication date in September 2019;
- "Identities" here refers to the lot ID of the wafers.

sql:
SELECT AVG(w.wafer_thickness) AS AverageThickness
FROM wafers w
INNER JOIN defects d ON w.wafer_id = d.wafer_id;

SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM wafers 
WHERE lot_id = '0';
